{
  "stem": "19969.6",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 78.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "See, Ernst Rohm's Brown Shirts was a civilian organization who were-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --were supported by German industrialists, Krapp and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They wanted to get rid of the Versailles Treaty and rearm Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And Hitler and the Brown Shirts were-- there were having to do that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Well, the Brown Shirts were well equipped.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were in uniform-- they wore a brown uniform.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were well equipped.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were just like an army and they were much larger than the German Army.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So when Hitler came to power, the German general says, we-- we're not going to support you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We can't put up with a civilian army.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So Hitler agreed to get rid of the Brown Shirts, but he took many of them with him-- with him, of course, like Goebbels and Goring and-- but Ernst Rohm, who was the head of the Brown Shirts, Hitler had executed.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "In one swoop he took out all the Brown Shirts that he did not like and they were disbanded.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But Hitler double-crossed the generals because he turned around and created the SS outside of the German army.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I refused to go because at that time, I was a district attorney over in western Colorado and I felt that I could not contribute really anything at all because what I saw, thousands of other people saw and had been photographed.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And besides, the incident of our killing the German guards would have not looked good on cross-examination.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I refused to go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, they had no jurisdiction over me at all, an American citizen here in this country.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The war crimes tribunal had no jurisdiction over me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Were you subpoenaed or just requested to go?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I got a subpoena from the United States Marshall.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
